operations.CreateBackend: This operation creates a backend for an Amplify app. Backends are automatically created at the time of app creation.
operations.CreateBackendConfig: Creates a config object for a backend.
operations.CreateToken: Generates a one-time challenge code to authenticate a user into your Amplify Admin UI.
operations.DeleteBackend: Removes an existing environment from your Amplify project.
operations.DeleteToken: Deletes the challenge token based on the given appId and sessionId.
operations.GenerateBackendAPIModels: Generates a model schema for an existing backend API resource.
operations.GetBackend: Provides project-level details for your Amplify UI project.
operations.GetBackendAPI: Gets the details for a backend API.
operations.GetBackendAPIModels: Generates a model schema for existing backend API resource.
operations.GetToken: Gets the challenge token based on the given appId and sessionId.
operations.ListBackendJobs: Lists the jobs for the backend of an Amplify app.
operations.RemoveAllBackends: Removes all backend environments from your Amplify project.
operations.RemoveBackendConfig: Removes the AWS resources that are required to access the Amplify Admin UI.
operations.UpdateBackendConfig: Updates the AWS resources that are required to access the Amplify Admin UI.
